11.35 am Australia have earned a 73-run lead after an hour and a half's worth of good work this morning. Nathan Lyon was going to be key with the Adelaide pitch roughing up. He's claimed three of the five wickets that fell today and has looked immensely impressive. India's bowlers will need to show they've settled down from the first-innings. Their batsmen haven't done too badly and will hope it wasn't all for naught
